foliation.note: Numbering in pencil in the upper right-hand corner of the first leaf of each quire, possibly by M.R. James. Full foliation added after digitisation.

collation.p:
The manuscript comprises one quire composed of four leaves and one of two leaves, followed by twelve quires composed of eight leaves. There is one leaf missing in quire 14.
Quire 14 (ff. 1-4)
Quire 22 (ff. 5-6)
Quire 38 (ff. 7-14)
Quire 48 (ff. 15-22)
Quire 58 (ff. 23-30)
Quire 68 (ff. 31-38)
Quire 78 (ff. 39-46)
Quire 88 (ff. 47-54)
Quire 98 (ff. 55-62)
Quire 108 (ff. 63-70)
Quire 118 (ff. 71-78)
Quire 128 (ff. 79-86)
Quire 138 (ff. 87-94)
Quire 148-1 (ff. 95-101: last leaf missing)

p.signatures: Quires numbered 1-13 in a 20th-century hand (quires 1-2 counted as one quire).

layout.seg: Two columns, 30 lines, frame and lines ruled in brown crayon. Pricked in the inner margins (the outer margins trimmed). Written above top line. Some columns have last words flourished with pen-drawings.

handNote.p: Protogothic bookhand; quotations flagged by marginal diples shaped like ‘s’; various symbols in margins (positura, signes-de-renvoi).

decoNote.p: Arabesque initials in red and green (e.g. P, 19 ll., f. 1r; C, 4 ll., f. 66v; Q, 5 ll., f. 92v).
Plain initials in green (P, 5 ll., f. 93r; T, 3 ll., f. 101r).
One-line red Roman numerals in margins for chapters.

additions.note: Occasional nota marks. Marginal notes in at least two different hands on ff. 12v, 16v, 46v, 56v and 65r. A late-15th-century note in the upper margin of f. 44r reads 'Hic incipietur in refectorio.'
Table of contents in a 17th-century hand on verso of one of the previous flyleaves.

binding.p: Rebound in 20th-century archival calfskin, sewn on two bands.
Previous 16th-century binding sewn on four bands. Flyleaves from this binding now kept separately, sewn together in a paper wrapper.

recordHist.source: This catalogue entry draws on the description in M.R. James, A descriptive catalogue of the western manuscripts in the library of Queens' College, Cambridge (Cambridge, 1905).

availability.p: For further information on the availability of the manuscript, please contact Queens' Old Library and Special Collections.
